## Impact Analysis

| Impact Area | Description |
|---|---|
| **Account Takeover Risk** | Any actor can create a My Muse account using another person's real email address. The legitimate owner receives no notification and is effectively blocked from registering with their own email. |
| **Subscription Fraud** | A user can initiate or complete a subscription purchase using an email they do not own. Payment confirmations and receipts are sent to an inaccessible address, creating billing and chargeback risk. |
| **Broken Account Recovery** | Users who mistype their email during sign-in have no recovery path — support and reset communications go to an address they cannot access. |
| **Data Integrity** | My Muse cannot reliably contact its user base. Transactional emails, subscription notices, and marketing communications will fail to reach real users. |
| **Ad Tracking on Unverified Users** | `capi_config` with `external_id` is assigned at account creation — unverified users are immediately enrolled in Facebook CAPI ad tracking. |
| **Industry Standard Violation** | Email verification on account creation is a universal security baseline (Netflix, Spotify, YouTube, Apple ID). The current implementation does not meet this standard. |

